topic: History Workflow Series ("Cultural Movements explorative search")

goals.1: Identify the BGP for Cultural Movement
goals.2: Identify the BGP for Renassaince, Baroque and Romanticism
goals.3: Identify the BGP for composer, painter, sculptor and poet
goals.4: Consider Renaissance, Baroque and Romanticism. Find how many composers, painters, sculptors and poets belong to those cultural movements (the results set must be a list of triples movement, job, #people)
goals.5: Find how many sculptures were made in Italy during Renaissance, Baroque, and Romanticism movements. Please consider all the sculptures and all the sculpture subtypes. (the result set must be a list of triples movement IRI, label and #sculptures).
goals.6: For each European country find how many poets belong to Romanticism (the result set must be a list of triples country IRI, label and #poets).
goals.7: Find the number of sculptures in the Louvre Museum belonging to Renaissance, Baroque, or Romanticism (return a number for each movement) (the result set must be a list of triples movement IRI, label and #sculptures).

name: workflow1_6

1.narrative:
startup the evaluation
setup the file and create the empty json
look at the properties of Donatello
output: British Museum person or institution ID
Biographical Dictionary of Italian People ID
National Gallery of Art artist ID
Union List of Artist Names ID
on focus list of Wikimedia project

1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?name WHERE { wd:Q37562 wdt:P135 ?obj . ?obj sc:name ?name. }

1.narrative: look at the properties of these movement

1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?name WHERE { wd:Q1472236 wdt:P361 ?obj . ?obj sc:name ?name. }
SELECT DISTINCT ?inst ?name WHERE { wd:Q1472236 wdt:P361 ?obj . ?obj wdt:P31 ?inst. ?inst sc:name ?name. }

2.narrative:
insert the result of TASK 1 in the file
list instances of cultural movements
2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?name WHERE { ?obj wdt:P31 wd:Q2198855. ?obj sc:name ?name. FILTER(REGEX(?name,"[B,b]aroque") || REGEX(?name,"[R,r]enaiss") || REGEX(?name,"[R,r]omant") ) . }
SELECT ?mov ?name WHERE { VALUES ?mov {wd:Q37068 wd:Q37853 wd:Q4692}. ?mov sc:name ?name. }

3.narrative: starts with Baroque and check how people is connected with it
3.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { ?people wdt:P31 wd:Q5. ?people ?prop wd:Q37853. ?prop sc:name ?name. }

3.narrative: let see properties of people. Use Donatello to speed up the search
3.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { wd:Q37562 ?prop ?x. FILTER(!isLiteral(?x)). ?prop sc:name ?name. }
output: on focus list of Wikimedia project

3.narrative: starts with Baroque and check how people is connected with
3.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?x ?name WHERE { ?people wdt:P31 wd:Q5. ?people wdt:P135 wd:Q37853. ?people wdt:P106 ?x. ?x sc:name ?name. FILTER(REGEX(?name,"[S,s]culpt") || REGEX(?name,"[P,p]oet") || REGEX(?name,"[C,c]ompos") || REGEX(?name,"[P,p]aint") ) }
SELECT ?jobs ?jName WHERE { VALUES ?jobs {wd:Q36834 wd:Q49757 wd:Q1281618 wd:Q1028181} . ?jobs sc:name ?jName. }

4.query: SELECT ?jobs ?jName ?movements ?mName COUNT(DISTINCT ?people) AS ?peop WHERE { VALUES ?movements {wd:Q37068 wd:Q37853 wd:Q4692} . VALUES ?jobs {wd:Q36834 wd:Q49757 wd:Q1281618 wd:Q1028181} . ?people wdt:P135 ?movements. ?people wdt:P106 ?jobs. ?jobs sc:name ?jName. ?movements sc:name ?mName. } GROUP BY ?jobs ?jName ?movements ?mName

5.narrative:
more elements mixed between URI and literals
add the year element
add the director element
First of all, find sculptures starting from sculptors
5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { VALUES ?movements {wd:Q37068 wd:Q37853 wd:Q4692} . ?people wdt:P135 ?movements; wdt:P106 wd:Q1281618. ?x ?prop ?people. ?prop sc:name ?name. }
output: said to be the same as

5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?x ?name WHERE { VALUES ?movements {wd:Q37068 wd:Q37853 wd:Q4692} . ?people wdt:P135 ?movements; wdt:P106 wd:Q1281618. ?x wdt:P170 ?people. ?x sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 20
output: The Virgin and Child with Saint Elizabeth and Saint John the Baptist
The Descent from the Cross by Peter Paul Rubens (Saint-Omer)
Young man with a black hat

5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?inst ?name WHERE { VALUES ?movements {wd:Q37068 wd:Q37853 wd:Q4692} . ?people wdt:P135 ?movements; wdt:P106 wd:Q1281618. ?x wdt:P170 ?people. ?x wdt:P31 ?inst. ?inst sc:name ?name. FILTER(REGEX(?name,"[S,s]culp")). }

5.narrative: list some sculpture using the subclasses
5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?x ?name WHERE { VALUES ?movements {wd:Q37068 wd:Q37853 wd:Q4692} . ?people wdt:P135 ?movements; wdt:P106 wd:Q1281618. ?x wdt:P170 ?people. ?x wdt:P31/wdt:P279* wd:Q860861. ?x sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 10
output: Bust of a Young noble lady
David with the head of Goliath

5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { VALUES ?movements {wd:Q37068 wd:Q37853 wd:Q4692} . ?people wdt:P135 ?movements; wdt:P106 wd:Q1281618. ?x wdt:P170 ?people. ?x wdt:P31/wdt:P279* wd:Q860861. ?x ?prop ?y. ?prop sc:name ?name. FILTER(REGEX(?name,"locate")). }
output: located in the administrative territorial entity

5.narrative: identify what is in the located in the administrative territory
5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?y ?name WHERE { VALUES ?movements {wd:Q37068 wd:Q37853 wd:Q4692} . ?people wdt:P135 ?movements; wdt:P106 wd:Q1281618. ?x wdt:P170 ?people. ?x wdt:P31/wdt:P279* wd:Q860861. ?x wdt:P131 ?y. ?y sc:name ?name. } limit 20

5.narrative: identify what is in the located in the administrative territory
5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?c ?name WHERE { VALUES ?movements {wd:Q37068 wd:Q37853 wd:Q4692} . ?people wdt:P135 ?movements; wdt:P106 wd:Q1281618. ?x wdt:P170 ?people. ?x wdt:P31/wdt:P279* wd:Q860861. ?x wdt:P131 ?y. ?y wdt:P17 ?c. ?c sc:name ?name. } limit 20

SELECT DISTINCT ?movements ?name COUNT(DISTINCT ?x) AS ?sculptures WHERE { VALUES ?movements {wd:Q37068 wd:Q37853 wd:Q4692} . ?people wdt:P135 ?movements; wdt:P106 wd:Q1281618. OPTIONAL{ ?x wdt:P170 ?people; wdt:P31/wdt:P279* wd:Q860861; wdt:P131 ?city. ?city wdt:P17 wd:Q38. } ?movements sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?movements ?name

6.narrative:
single literal associated to an URI
find poet of romanticism
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?people ?name ?country ?cName WHERE { ?people wdt:P135 wd:Q37068; wdt:P106 wd:Q49757; wdt:P27 ?country. ?country sc:name ?cName. ?people sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 10
SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { ?people wdt:P135 wd:Q37068; wdt:P106 wd:Q49757; wdt:P27 ?country. ?country ?prop ?c. ?prop sc:name ?name. FILTER(REGEX(?name,"[C,c]ontin")). }
SELECT DISTINCT ?c ?name WHERE { ?people wdt:P135 wd:Q37068; wdt:P106 wd:Q49757; wdt:P27 ?country. ?country wdt:P30 ?c. ?c sc:name ?name. }

SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?name COUNT(DISTINCT ?people) AS ?poets WHERE { ?people wdt:P135 wd:Q37068; wdt:P106 wd:Q49757; wdt:P27 ?country. ?country wdt:P30 wd:Q46. ?country sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?country ?name
output: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland

7.narrative:
single literal associated to an URI
I found the property location P276, now I modify the previous query to get all the sculptures that are in the louvre museum.
7.query: SELECT ?movement ?movementsName (COUNT(DISTINCT ?sculptures) AS ?scul) WHERE { OPTIONAL{ ?sculptures wdt:P31/wdt:P279* wd:Q860861 . ?sculptures wdt:P276 wd:Q19675. ?sculptures wdt:P135 ?movement . } VALUES ?movement { wd:Q4692 wd:Q37853 wd:Q37068} ?movement sc:name ?movementsName . } GROUP BY ?movement ?movementsName LIMIT 10
